HEADWORD: Orthomorphic
<hw>Or`tho*mor"phic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ortho-</ets> + <ets>morphic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>
<def>Having the right form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Orthomorphic projection</b></col>, <cd>a projection in
which the angles in the figure to be projected are equal to the
corresponding angles in the projected figure.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

